
# Introduction

During holiday seasons and other Liturgical observances, many start to argue about wether it is a part of our Christian faith to observe these traditions. They argue that these observances are man-made traditions and not a legitimate part of our faith. But is this really the case? As we will see in this article, there are arguments to be made for each Church to set a Liturgical calendar. This does not mean that these observances have no meaning or are illegitimate festivities. On the contrary, they add and enrich our passed down Christian faith with all of its traditions. 

# Christ our Archetype

